      • add

        int add(byte[] marking,
        int newIndex)
        Add a marking to the set of visited markings. If it already exists, return it's number, otherwise add it and return newIndex
        Parameters:
        marking - the byte[] indicating the number of tokens per place
        Returns:
        the id of the marking in the set. If the marking existed before, the existing ID is returned, otherwise a new successive ID is returned.
